check_and_fix_golay_24_6: Attempts to correct an hex (6-bit) word using the Golay(24,12,8) FEC.
check_and_fix_golay_24_12: Attempts to correct a 12-bit word using the Golay(24,12,8) FEC.
encode_golay_24_6: Encodes an hex word using the Golay(24,12,8) FEC.
encode_golay_24_12: Encodes an 12-bitword using the Golay(24,12,8) FEC.
check_and_fix_redsolomon_36_20_17: Attempts to correct 20 hex words using the Reed-Solomon(36,20,17) FEC.
encode_reedsolomon_36_20_17: Calculates the Reed-Solomon parity of 20 words of 6 bits each.
check_and_fix_hamming_10_6_3: Attempts to error correct a hex (6-bit) word using the Hamming(10,6,3) FEC.
encode_hamming_10_6_3: Encodes an hex word with the Hamming(10,6,3) FEC.
check_and_fix_reedsolomon_24_12_13: Attempts to correct 12 hex words using the Reed-Solomon(24,12,13) FEC.
encode_reedsolomon_24_12_13: Encodes 12 hex words with the Reed-Solomon(24,12,13) FEC.
check_and_fix_reedsolomon_24_16_9: Attempts to correct 16 hex words using the Reed-Solomon(24,16,9) FEC.
encode_reedsolomon_24_16_9: Encodes 12 hex words with the Reed-Solomon(24,16,9) FEC.
check_NID: Checks a NID value, returns the fixed NAC, DUID and also an indication if it failed to decode the NID.
read_dibit: Reads a dibit (two bits) from the stream of data. Takes into account the periodic occurrence of status bits that show up every 36 dibits. Status bits are discarded.
read_dibit_update_analog_data: Reads a number of dibits and stores its value together with the actual analog value that has been intrepreted as the dibit into an AnalogSignal structure. This is used later in the P25 heuristics module to improve the accuracy of the digitizer.
read_word: Reads a word, made up of length bits or length/2 dibits. Also keeps track of the status dibits.
read_hamm_parity: Reads 4 bits from the stream of data. Those are the parity bits that follow each hex word.
read_golay24_parity: Reads 12 bits from the stream of data. Those are the extended Golay parity bits that follow a word of data.
read_zeros: Reads bits from the data stream that should all be zeros. This is valuable information for the heuristics module and we update it.
estimate_symbol: Important method that estimates the most likely symbol for a given analog signal value and previous dibit. This is called by the digitizer.
contribute_to_heuristics: This method contributes valuable information from dibits whose value we are confident is correct. We take the dibits and corresponding analog signal values to model the Gaussians for each dibit (and previous dibit if enabled).
update_error_stats: Updates the estimate for the BER (bit error rate). Mind this is method is not called for every single bit in the data stream but only for those bits over which we have an estimate of its error rate, specifically the bits that are protected by Reed-Solomon codes.
get_P25_BER_estimate: Returns the estimate for the BER (bit error rate).
process_IMBE: Separate imbe frames and deinterleave. This important methods read the IMBE data from the stream and passes it to the vocoder to produce audio.
read_and_correct_hex_word: Reads an hex word, its parity bits and attempts to error correct it using the Hamming FEC.
correct_hamming_dibits: Correct the information in analog_signal_array according with the content of data, which has been error corrected and should be valid.
